    List distributions

    list_distributions.Rd

    List distributions included in package

    Usage

    list_distributions(
  delay_dist = c("all", "incubation", "onset_to_admission", "onset_to_death",
    "serial_interval", "generation_time"),
  parameters = FALSE
)

    Arguments

    delay_dist

    A character defining parameter to be listed: "all" "incubation", "onset_to_admission", "onset_to_death", or "serial_interval". "all" will not filter by a certain delay distribution and return all records. "all" is the default.

    parameters

    A logical defining whether to show parameter values, default is FALSE

    Author

    Adam Kucharski

    Examples

# metrics can be chosen using the `delay_dist` argument, for example
# incubation period or onset to death
list_distributions(delay_dist = "incubation")

# full table including extra information (e.g. parameters of the
